The paper discusses privacy issues in recommender systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a solution using differential privacy, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and databases (cs.DB) to protect sensitive information. The paper also involves probabilistic modeling, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
